From 4a39b823ba8bc040e0178f38eb90320319a305be Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Alex (tuisang)" <alex2000rui@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 11:02:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] rebrand: Atelier Modern design system + Black Steel Crew
 content cleanup

- Migrate globals.css, layout.tsx, and all components/pages from Heritage &
  Grain (dark green/oak) and the leftover dark cyberpunk Black Steel Crew
  theme onto the Atelier Modern palette (cream/burnt-orange, Libre Franklin,
  Material Symbols) per DESIGN.md
- Rebuild homepage, booking, portfolio, and quote pages to match the Stitch
  design reference and fix wood-craft content
- Replace steel/gates/railings/welding copy with woodworking content across
  catalog, reviews, ai-artisan, dashboard, checkout, contact, admin,
  chat-history, cart, blog, not-found, loading, error, services, payments
- Fix wrong M-Pesa STK callback domain (was pointing at
  blacksteelcrew.tuistech.co.ke, breaking payment confirmation)
- Fix wrong sitemap/robots/canonical domains across page metadata
- Fix Black Steel Crew branding in transactional emails (lib/email.ts)
- Remove stray duplicate app/api/admin/page.tsx with stale admin Clerk ID
- Fix two pre-existing broken <a> tags in services/page.tsx and
  payments/page.tsx that would have failed next build
- Make booking/quote API routes accept the rebuilt forms' field names
